--- Context-assembly Phase 0, invariant 5: provenance completeness. Companion to
--- spec/context-assembly-tracker.md (Decision 5) and spec/agent-harness.md,
--- which requires that every injected context bundle must record provenance in
--- the evidence store. Assembly is provenance-gated: a bundle records a durable
--- evidence row
--- before it is placed into the sent system prompt, and there is no path from an
--- unrecorded bundle to the prompt. The safety property modeled here: a bundle
--- with no provenance source (`untracked`) never reaches `assembled`. There is
--- deliberately no rule assembling a staged/untracked bundle directly, so every
--- assembled bundle carries evidence.
mod WHIPPLESCRIPT-PROVENANCE-COMPLETENESS is
  sorts Cfg .

  op none : -> Cfg [ctor] .
  op __ : Cfg Cfg -> Cfg [ctor assoc comm id: none] .

  op staged : -> Cfg [ctor] .      --- a bundle staged for assembly
  op recorded : -> Cfg [ctor] .    --- its provenance has been recorded
  op evidence : -> Cfg [ctor] .    --- the durable provenance row
  op assembled : -> Cfg [ctor] .   --- the bundle placed in the sent system prompt
  op untracked : -> Cfg [ctor] .   --- fixture: a bundle with no provenance source

  --- Recording a staged bundle's provenance emits a durable evidence row and
  --- marks it recorded...
  rl [record] : staged => recorded evidence .

  --- ...and only a recorded bundle is assembled into the prompt. There is no rule
  --- assembling `staged`/`untracked` directly -- assembly is provenance-gated,
  --- which is what the untracked bite proves.
  rl [assemble] : recorded => assembled .
endm
